race.description: Langhorne Creek Wine Region Vignerons Cup Handicap
race.comment: Pretty even with almost all having some sort of claim on best. DANCING STORM (3) has been knocking on the door with placings at three of last five. Was below best two back in the same race as HYPERNOVA then last start got home hard to place in a BM86 in town. This trip suits and looks hard to beat on best figures. HYPERNOVA (4) was fourth two back in a BM70 then runner-up in a BM68, both at Morphettville. Close to another win and although first try this longer trip should be winding up strongly. SACHEM (8) was beaten a fair way over a mile in town latest. Previous form stacks right up though and worth another try.  TRUFFLE FINDER (7) has been getting back and running on late in far richer races lately. Going better than it looks and gets chance in this line-up to find some form.
